        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 1:19PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 119 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles north of Pickens, or 4 miles south of Table Rock State Park,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pickens, Travelers Rest, Slater-Marietta, Paris Mountain State Park,
Tigerville, Lake Robinson, Pleasant Ridge State Park, Table Rock
State Park, Furman University, and Jones Gap State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
